Law of The Republic of Uzbekistan
On official statistics
Adopted by the Legislative Chamber on May 7, 2021 
Approved by the Senate on June 26, 2021
Chapter 1. General Provisions
Article 1. Purpose of this Law
The purpose of this Law shall be the regulation of relations in the area of official statistics. Article 2. Scope of application of this Law
This Law shall apply to producers and users of official statistics, respondents and providers of administrative data, as well as to the relations arising between them, related to the production, dissemination, and coordination of official statistics. This Law shall not apply to statistics that is not considered as official. Article 3. Legislation on official statistics
The legislation on official statistics shall include this Law and other legislative acts. Should an international treaty of the Republic of Uzbekistan stipulate the rules other than those provided for by the legislation of the Republic of Uzbekistan on official statistics, the rules of the international treaty shall apply. Article 4. Basic concepts
The following basic concepts shall be used in this Law:
identifier is a sequence of characters that allows identifying a statistical unit based on its name, geographic location, or other specific properties;
individual data is primary data characterizing a statistical unit, which allows identifying it either directly or indirectly;
administrative data is data generated by state administration and economic management bodies, as well as local executive authorities in connection with the exercise of their powers;
metadata is data that describes statistical data and processes in a standardized way by providing users with information about data sources, methodologies, definitions, classifications, and quality;
national statistical system is a set of state statistical bodies and other producers of official statistics that jointly produce and disseminate official statistics;
producer of official statistics is the state administration body and (or) its subdivision that is part of the national statistical system that produces statistical data in accordance with statistical programs in the field of official statistics;
statistical data is information of economic, demographic, social, financial, environmental and other nature, produced as a result of statistical observations and (or) on the basis of administrative data;
production of statistical data is the activity pertaining to collecting, processing, summarizing, analyzing, disseminating, and storing statistical data;
statistical unit is an individual or a legal entity (including its separate subdivisions, branches, and representative offices) or a household subject to statistical observation;
classification is the division of sets of objects by similarity or distinction into separate subsets in accordance with the accepted methods and attributes in the field of official statistics. Article 5. Official statistics
Official statistics are the statistical data produced and disseminated by state statistical agencies and other producers of official statistics in accordance with the provisions of this Law. Article 6. Key Principles of official statistics
The key principles of official statistics shall be as follows:
independence;
clarity and transparency;
accuracy and reliability;
impartiality and objectivity;
statistical confidentiality;
relevance. Chapter 2. Regulation of Official Statistics
Article 7. Main areas of the state policy in the field of official statistics
The following shall represent main areas of the state policy in the field of official statistics:
improving the legal and organizational basis of the national statistical system;
improving the infrastructure of the national statistical system;
increasing the opportunities to use modern information and communication technologies;
expanding and strengthening international cooperation. Article 8. Powers of the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan in the field of official statistics
The Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan shall:
ensure the implementation of state policy in the field of official statistics;
determine the priorities for the development of official statistics;с
ensure the development, approval and implementation of statistical programs in the field of official statistics (hereinafter – the statistical programs);
take measures to ensure that the area of official statistics is interconnected with targeted government programs. The Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan may also exercise other powers in accordance with the legislation. Article 9. Powers of the State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics in the field of official statistics
The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics shall be the authorized state body in the field of official statistics (hereinafter – the authorized state body).

The authorized state body shall:
implement the state policy in the field of official statistics;
coordinate the development of statistical programs and monitor their implementation;
implement the priority areas for the development of official statistics jointly with other producers of official statistics;
coordinate the official statistics development activities within the national statistical system;
conduct an audit of the statistical methodologies of other producers of official statistics for compliance with international recommendations;
develop, approve, and introduce the statistical methodologies and statistical observation forms complying with international recommendations;
establish the exchange of statistical data and metadata with the producers of official statistics;
integrate with information systems of state administration and economic management bodies, as well as local executive authorities to conduct statistical observations, establish and analyze official statistical data;
develop and maintain statistical registers for the organization and conduct of statistical observations, as well as for their use for other statistical purposes;
establish advisory and working groups to conduct organizational and methodological work in the field of official statistics;
develop measures for the coordinated dissemination of official statistics within the national statistical system;
develop a uniform terminology in the field of official statistics in coordination with other producers of official statistics;
coordinate the work on training, retraining, and advanced training of personnel in the field of official statistics;
carry out the international cooperation in the field of official statistics. The specially authorized state body may also exercise other powers in accordance with the legislation. Article 10. Statistical Council
The Statistical Council shall be a collegial advisory body for the development, functioning, and coordination of official statistics under the authorized state body. The Statistical Council shall be composed of representatives of state administration bodies, research organizations, nongovernmental non-profit organizations, and national statistical experts. The composition of the Statistical Council shall be approved by the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan. The working body of the Statistical Council shall be the relevant division of the authorized state body. Article 11. Coordination of the activities of producers of official statistics
When producing statistics, producers of official statistics shall be guided by internationally recommended definitions, classifications, and methodology. The authorized state body shall coordinate the activities of other producers of official statistics under statistical programs. The producers of official statistics shall coordinate the methodology of statistical data production within the scope of their powers. In case of detection of a non-compliance with international recommendations in the statistical methodologies of other producers of official statistics, the authorized state body shall – on the results of the audit of statistical methodologies – have the right to make compulsory representations to them. Other producers of official statistics, being a part of the national statistical system, shall establish subdivisions responsible for generating statistical data and ensuring information exchange with the authorized state body. Producers of official statistics and providers of administrative data shall provide the authorized state body with the statistical and (or) administrative data available to them on a free-of-charge basis in accordance with the procedure and within the time-frame established by the statistical programs. Chapter 3. Rights and obligations of producers of official statistics, respondents, administrative data providers and users of official statistics
Article 12. Producers of official statistics
State statistics bodies shall be the main producers of official statistics. The state administration bodies included in the statistical programs as producers of official statistics shall be other producers of official statistics. Producers of official statistics shall produce, disseminate, and coordinate official statistics in accordance with this Law and statistical programs. Article 13. State statistics bodies
The state statistics bodies shall be the authorized state body, Departments of Statistics of the Republic of Karakalpakstan, regions and Tashkent city, Divisions of Statistics of districts (cities). State bodies, other organizations, and their officials shall not have the right to interfere with the activities of state statistics bodies carried out in accordance with this Law. The Departments of Statistics of the Republic of Karakalpakstan, regions, and Tashkent city, Divisions of Statistics of districts (cities) shall be independent from the local state authorities and shall be directly subordinated to the authorized state body. Financing and the material and technical support of the activities of state statistics bodies shall be provided from the State Budget of the Republic of Uzbekistan in accordance with the statistical programs and other sources not prohibited by law. Article 14.

Rights and obligations of the state statistics bodies
State statistics bodies shall have the right to:
obtain statistical observation forms from state administration and economic management bodies, citizens' self-government bodies, banks, and other organizations, and use statistical observation data for statistical purposes;
conduct statistical observations of the activities of statistical units and use the primary data obtained for statistical purposes;
give incentives to respondent individuals for participation in statistical observations;
request and receive from the state administration and economic management bodies, as well as from other organizations the information necessary for the implementation of statistical programs;
engage individuals and legal entities on a contractual basis to collect statistical data necessary for the production of official statistics, in accordance with the legislation;
use and implement in the national statistical system the modern methods and tools for collecting, processing, summarizing, analyzing, disseminating, and storing statistical data;
in the case of violations related to submission of statistical data, give instructions to correct them and make the respective corrections to the statistical data;
apply – within the scope of its powers – the administrative penalties in accordance with the law to the officials who violated the procedure for submitting statistical reports. The state statistics bodies may also have other rights in accordance with the legislation. The state statistics bodies shall be obliged to:
ensure compliance with the key principles of official statistics and the unity of statistical methodologies corresponding to international recommendations;
organize statistical observations on the implementation of state programs for socio-economic development of the country, territories, industries, and spheres;
organize and ensure the collection of statistical data, statistical observations of households, conducting censuses, one-time counts, sample surveys, and other statistical observations;
ensure the implementation of statistical programs;
provide statistical data to state regulatory and administration bodies;
make international and interregional statistical comparisons;
ensure maintaining statistical registers and a system of classifications for statistical purposes. The state statistics bodies may also bear other obligations in accordance with the legislation. Article 15. Rights and obligations of other producers of official statistics
Other producers of official statistics shall have the right to:
choose primary data sources, obtain and collect data required to produce official statistics directly from respondents;
provide incentives to respondent individuals for participation in statistical observations;
establish methods for respondents to collect primary data. Other producers of official statistics may also have other rights in accordance with the legislation. Other producers of official statistics shall be obliged to:
ensure compliance with the key principles of official statistics and the unity of statistical methodologies corresponding to international recommendations;
ensure the implementation of statistical programs;
collect primary data, taking into account the quality of statistics, the cost of providing data, and the burden on respondents;
process, disseminate, and store the collected data in accordance with the provisions of this Law and the Law of the Republic of Uzbekistan "On Personal Data";
inform respondents about the purpose and legal basis of the statistical observations, as well as their rights, obligations, and confidentiality of the individual data obtained. Other producers of official statistics may also have other obligations in accordance with the legislation. Article 16. Respondents
A respondent shall be an individual or a legal entity that provides official statistics producers with individual and other data for statistical purposes. Respondents shall have the right to receive explanations and information from producers of official statistics about the purpose and legal basis of statistical observations, as well as information about ensuring confidentiality of individual data obtained. When conducting statistical observations according to statistical programs, respondents – with the exception of cases stipulated by part five of this Article, shall be obliged to:
provide the producers of official statistics with reliable and complete data on a free-of-charge basis in accordance with the procedure and within the time-frame established by the producer of official statistics;
correct, update, supplement, and submit data to the producers of official statistics within the time-frame established by them, if according to their findings or the findings of the producers of official statistics the data submitted is not correct, not up-to-date and (or) incomplete. Respondents may provide statistics to the producers of official statistics in paper or electronic form. In this case, the methods of statistical data collection shall be established by the producers of official statistics. Respondents participating in the censuses conducted in certain areas of demographic and socio-economic development of the country shall have the right to provide reliable individual data according to the form of the census paper and shall be obliged not to hinder the census processes. Article 17. Providers of administrative data
The providers of administrative data shall include the state administration and economic management bodies, as well as local executive authorities that provide administrative data to producers of official statistics. Providers of administrative data that own databases of individuals and legal entities shall have the right - within the scope of their powers – to:
form individual data on matters within the scope of their powers for administrative purposes;
choose primary data sources for the formation of administrative data;
establish data collection methods, obtain, and collect the necessary data directly from individuals or legal entities, and households.

Providers of administrative data that own databases of individuals and legal entities shall be obliged to provide producers of official statistics on free-of-charge basis with the following:
administrative data at their disposal;
metadata to assess the quality of statistical data. Provision of administrative data to producers of official statistics shall be carried out according to the forms and periodicity established in the annual statistical program. Article 18. Users of official statistics
Users of official statistics may be individuals or legal entities (including their separate subdivisions, branches, and representative offices). Users of official statistics shall have the right to:
freely use statistical data published on official websites of producers of official statistics and in the media;
request the producers of official statistics to obtain open statistical data that is not published on official websites and in the media, or propose their publication. Users of official statistics shall be obliged to indicate the sources of statistical data that they have used in their products (works and services). Access to individual data and confidential data for research purposes shall be provided in accordance with the procedure stipulated in Articles 30 and 31 of this Law. Chapter 4. Statistical programs, observations and registers, censuses, procedure for their preparation and approval
Article 19. Statistical programs
The authorized state body shall ensure the preparation of statistical programs in cooperation with other producers of official statistics, users of official statistics, respondents and providers of administrative data. Statistical programs shall be submitted to the Statistical Council for review. The authorized state body jointly with other producers of official statistics that are part of the national statistical system shall ensure the implementation of statistical programs. Statistical programs can be multi-year and annual. Article 20. Multi-year statistical program
The multi-year statistical program shall be developed as a whole for the national statistical system and determine the strategic areas of development of official statistics. The multi-annual statistical program shall consist of the concept, strategic objectives, and priority areas of development of the national statistical system, as well as mechanisms of implementation of program measures for the development of official statistics. Article 21. Annual statistical program
The annual statistical program shall be developed to implement the multi-year statistical program. The annual statistical program shall include the following tasks:
determination of priority areas for the development of official statistics;
organization of statistical observations to be carried out by producers of official statistics;
preparation and provision of administrative data to producers of official statistics;
development and maintenance of statistical registers;
dissemination of official statistics. The annual statistical program shall include a list of statistical data produced and disseminated by each producer of official statistics, indicating the periodicity and terms of their production. Article 22. Approval and funding of statistical programs
Multi-year and annual statistical programs after their consideration by the Statistical Council shall be submitted by the authorized state body to the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan and the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan, respectively, for approval. Multi-year statistical programs shall be approved by the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan, and annual statistical programs shall be approved by the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan. Producers of official statistics shall be provided with financial and material and technical resources to implement statistical programs. Funding of statistical programs shall be carried out at the expense of the State budget of the Republic of Uzbekistan and other sources, not prohibited by law. Funding of work not included in the statistical programs shall be carried out at the expense of individuals and legal entities initiating this work. Article 23. Statistical observations
Statistical observations shall be the processes of primary collection of individual and other respondent data conducted by producers of official statistics for statistical purposes using statistical methodologies. Statistical observations can be continuous and sampling-based, and must be carried out in accordance with statistical programs. Continuous statistical observations shall be carried out on the basis of statistical reporting forms approved by the authorized state body. Sampling-based statistical observations shall be conducted on the basis of statistical observation forms approved by the producers of official statistics. In sampling-based statistical observations carried out by producers of official statistics, respondents and households shall participate on a voluntary basis. Article 24. Censuses
The census shall be an action ensuring obtaining data on the number and structure of the population, housing, the structure and condition of economic units, and other data on a continuous basis. The census can be conducted on certain characteristics and areas of demographic and socio-economic development of the country, as well as carried out in the entire territory of the Republic of Uzbekistan or in certain areas of the country. Individual data of respondents shall be collected according to the questions set by the Census Program approved by the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan. Census data can be generated from statistical observations, administrative data, or a combination of both. Decision on conducting census with indication of date and term, as well as sources of financing shall be made by the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan on the proposal of the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan. Article 25.

